verses.text: And it came to pass after these things , that \add one\add* told Joseph , Behold, thy father \add is\add* sick : and he took with him his two sons , Manasseh and Ephraim.
And \add one\add* told Jacob , and said , Behold, thy son Joseph cometh unto thee: and Israel strengthened himself, and sat upon the bed.
And Jacob said unto Joseph , God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan , and blessed me,

And said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful , and multiply thee, and I will make of thee a multitude of people ; and will give this land to thy seed after thee \add for\add* an everlasting possession. \p
¶ And now thy two sons , Ephraim and Manasseh , which were born unto thee in the land of Egypt before I came unto thee into Egypt , \add are\add* mine; as Reuben and Simeon , they shall be mine.
And thy issue , which thou begettest after them, shall be thine, \add and\add* shall be called after the name of their brethren in their inheritance.

And as for me, when I came from Padan , Rachel died by me in the land of Canaan in the way , when yet \add there was\add* but a little way to come unto Ephrath : and I buried her there in the way of Ephrath ; the same \add is\add* Beth-lehem. \p
And Israel beheld Joseph’s sons , and said , Who \add are\add* these?
And Joseph said unto his father , They \add are\add* my sons , whom God hath given me in this \add place\add*. And he said , Bring them , I pray thee, unto me, and I will bless them.
Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age , \add so that\add* he could not see. And he brought them near unto him; and he kissed them, and embraced them.\f + \fr 48.10 \ft dim: Heb. heavy\f*
And Israel said unto Joseph , I had not thought to see thy face : and, lo, God hath shewed me also thy seed.
And Joseph brought them out from between his knees , and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.
And Joseph took them both , Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel’s left hand , and Manasseh in his left hand toward Israel’s right hand , and brought \add them\add* near unto him.

And Israel stretched out his right hand , and laid \add it\add* upon Ephraim’s head , who \add was\add* the younger , and his left hand upon Manasseh’s head , guiding his hands wittingly ; for Manasseh \add was\add* the firstborn. \p
¶ And he blessed Joseph , and said , God , before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac did walk , the God which fed me all my life long unto this day ,

The Angel which redeemed me from all evil , bless the lads ; and let my name be named on them, and the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac ; and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.\f + \fr 48.16 \ft grow: Heb. as fishes do increase\f*

And when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand upon the head of Ephraim , it displeased him: and he held up his father’s hand , to remove it from Ephraim’s head unto Manasseh’s head.\f + \fr 48.17 \ft displeased…: was evil in his eyes\f*
And Joseph said unto his father , Not so, my father : for this \add is\add* the firstborn ; put thy right hand upon his head.

And his father refused , and said , I know \add it\add*, my son , I know \add it:\add* he also shall become a people , and he also shall be great : but truly his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his seed shall become a multitude of nations.\f + \fr 48.19 \ft multitude: Heb. fulness\f*
And he blessed them that day , saying , In thee shall Israel bless , saying , God make thee as Ephraim and as Manasseh : and he set Ephraim before Manasseh.
And Israel said unto Joseph , Behold, I die : but God shall be with you, and bring you again unto the land of your fathers.
Moreover I have given to thee one portion above thy brethren , which I took out of the hand of the Amorite with my sword and with my bow.
